Let's plug $\blueD{a=-1}$, $\maroonD{b=3}$, and $\purpleC{f(x)=e^{x^2-2x}}$ into the formula:

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{\displaystyle\int_{\blueD a}^{\maroonD b} \purpleC{f(x)}\,dx}{\maroonD b-\blueD a}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{\displaystyle\int_{\blueD {-1}}^{\maroonD 3} \purpleC{e^{x^2-2x}}\,dx}{\maroonD 3-(\blueD{-1})}
\\\\
&=\dfrac14\displaystyle\int_{-1}^{3} e^{x^2-2x}\,dx
\end{align}$

Now we evaluate the definite integral, and then the entire expression, using a graphing calculator:

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{\approx}\dfrac14\goldD{\displaystyle\int_{-1}^{3} e^{x^2-2x}\,dx}
\\\\
&\approx \dfrac14\cdot\goldD{12.105}
\\\\
&\approx 3.026
\end{align}$

